00:04:37,330 --> 00:04:39,600
They are taking turns
to attack you and wear you out!

39
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:40,930
Over there! There he is!

40
00:07:22,090 --> 00:07:23,430
Shrimpie,

41
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,770
why are you here?

42
00:09:15,460 --> 00:09:22,020
[Archives: The Nanyang Mystery]

43
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:25,050
[Episode 10]

44
00:10:35,530 --> 00:10:36,360
Zhang Hailou,

45
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:38,300
you didn't disappoint me.

46
00:11:17,540 --> 00:11:18,540
It's all over now.

47
00:11:22,740 --> 00:11:24,310
What on earth happened here?

48
00:11:24,310 --> 00:11:25,840
Who wants to kill you?

49
00:11:25,940 --> 00:11:27,370
These men are clearly more

50
00:11:27,370 --> 00:11:28,620
than just robbers.

51
00:11:28,820 --> 00:11:29,860
Our deal

52
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:32,380
doesn't oblige me to explain it to you.

53
00:11:32,710 --> 00:11:34,840
Keep doing what you're supposed to do.

54
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:38,400
Who's this lady?

55
00:11:39,010 --> 00:11:40,960
She's more terrifying than a monster.

56
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:43,870
Does someone like her
really need our protection?

57
00:11:43,980 --> 00:11:45,390
It only means

58
00:11:45,410 --> 00:11:46,720
that her enemies are more formidable
than we think.

59
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,770
Tally up our losses.

60
00:11:47,770 --> 00:11:49,000
Next, we must take control.

61
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:51,240
Otherwise, the deal is pointless.

62
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:52,120
Do it.

63
00:11:52,510 --> 00:11:52,970
Come on.

64
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:22,800
[The Nan'an]

65
00:12:26,690 --> 00:12:31,690
[A few days later]

66
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:23,500
Those assassins have all been locked up.

67
00:13:23,940 --> 00:13:25,080
As for your friend's corpse,

68
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:27,280
Miss Dong said she would take care of it.

69
00:13:27,790 --> 00:13:28,810
So don't worry.

70
00:13:50,860 --> 00:13:52,660
They thought you were Steven,

71
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:55,290
so they gave you the best medicine.

72
00:13:55,890 --> 00:13:57,790
I didn't expect you to be so fit

73
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,410
and recover so quickly.

74
00:14:32,570 --> 00:14:34,500
You should at least eat something.

75
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:47,980
Actually, I still don't get it.

76
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,550
I mean, I am a stowaway.

77
00:14:53,310 --> 00:14:55,510
And we caused such a huge mess together.

78
00:14:56,970 --> 00:14:58,650
Why did she let us stay

79
00:15:00,390 --> 00:15:02,720
in such a nice suite
instead of killing us?

80
00:15:06,550 --> 00:15:07,220
Plague,

81
00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:09,410
actually...

82
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:13,170
Actually, I can understand how you feel.

83
00:15:16,870 --> 00:15:18,400
Before getting on the ship,

84
00:15:20,270 --> 00:15:21,820
my boss committed suicide
right in front of me

85
00:15:21,820 --> 00:15:23,880
because of the alcohol prohibition.

86
00:15:24,580 --> 00:15:27,510
I will never forget that scene
for the rest of my life.

87
00:15:28,670 --> 00:15:29,870
I had no other choice.

88
00:15:31,820 --> 00:15:32,630
With nowhere else to go,

89
00:15:32,630 --> 00:15:34,960
I had to head for Jinfan
to find my brother.

90
00:15:36,740 --> 00:15:38,080
What else could we do?

91
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:43,600
There are many things you can't hide from,
no matter how much you want to.

92
00:15:45,340 --> 00:15:47,540
But those left behind must keep living.

93
00:15:48,510 --> 00:15:50,460
We have to live well.

94
00:15:51,740 --> 00:15:53,540
And it's not just for ourselves.

95
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:57,030
Don't you

96
00:15:57,770 --> 00:15:59,620
have anyone you care about?

97
00:17:12,349 --> 00:17:12,980
Mentor,

98
00:17:13,810 --> 00:17:15,010
what are you drawing?

99
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:22,069
Your true nature is a snake.

100
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:22,980
A snake

101
00:17:23,300 --> 00:17:24,700
will devour everything.

102
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:29,120
You must overcome your true nature.

103
00:17:32,140 --> 00:17:34,200
Do you still remember what I told you?

104
00:17:34,810 --> 00:17:35,470
I remember.

105
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:36,140
Can you do it?

106
00:17:36,140 --> 00:17:36,740
I can.

107
00:17:36,740 --> 00:17:39,530
There's a big difference
between hearing it and doing it.

108
00:17:39,530 --> 00:17:41,420
When you finally manage to do it,

109
00:17:41,830 --> 00:17:43,490
that's when you pay the price.

110
00:17:44,050 --> 00:17:46,000
Only then will you know what I mean.

111
00:17:47,330 --> 00:17:48,950
But you are lucky,

112
00:17:49,310 --> 00:17:51,170
having Zhang Haixia by your side—

113
00:17:51,610 --> 00:17:52,880
he will remind you.

114
00:17:53,550 --> 00:17:54,550
Did you hear that?

115
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:56,010
Be nice to me.

116
00:18:06,610 --> 00:18:08,270
Put this on when I'm not around

117
00:18:09,570 --> 00:18:10,480
in the future.

118
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:12,670
Look at it before every action.

119
00:19:08,590 --> 00:19:09,310
Plague.

120
00:19:11,810 --> 00:19:12,460
Plague?

121
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:17,070
I'll just take a break.

122
00:19:17,070 --> 00:19:18,530
You go ahead and count.

123
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:21,810
We have to count them all today anyway.

124
00:19:24,550 --> 00:19:25,660
Bro, who are you?

125
00:19:26,220 --> 00:19:27,330
You can't come in here.

126
00:19:27,330 --> 00:19:29,530
Where are the robbers
who were on the ship earlier?

127
00:19:29,530 --> 00:19:30,870
Hey, who are you?

128
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:36,630
They're mostly all dead.

129
00:19:36,830 --> 00:19:38,360
Only a few of them are alive,

130
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:40,500
and they've been
locked up by Miss Dong.

131
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:41,530
After the ship docks,

132
00:19:41,530 --> 00:19:43,000
t-they will be handed over to the police.

133
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,400
Where are they locked up?

134
00:20:01,530 --> 00:20:02,760
Why are you so late?

135
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:06,260
And what the hell happened
to the bodies in those boxes?

136
00:20:06,610 --> 00:20:08,260
It takes like forever.

137
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:11,030
I don't know where these bodies came from.

138
00:20:11,180 --> 00:20:13,410
They've all been specially embalmed.

139
00:20:13,830 --> 00:20:15,220
God knows what these Easterners

140
00:20:15,220 --> 00:20:16,570
planned to do with them.

141
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:18,150
Well, see you later.

142
00:20:50,740 --> 00:20:53,310
You don't need to ask me
any more questions.

143
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:57,200
I don't know anything,

144
00:20:58,810 --> 00:21:01,200
and I won't say anything.

145
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:03,470
How did Zhang Haixia die?

146
00:21:30,010 --> 00:21:31,500
Zhang Haixia!

147
00:21:31,660 --> 00:21:33,620
How did he die?

148
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:55,710
Wait.

149
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:02,440
Which one

150
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:05,160
exactly are you asking about?

151
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:15,640
Zhang Haixia,

152
00:22:16,700 --> 00:22:17,900
who is in his twenties

153
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:20,720
and paralyzed in both legs.

154
00:22:33,250 --> 00:22:34,440
I know him.

155
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:36,930
He was very smart

156
00:22:37,850 --> 00:22:39,240
and very formidable.

157
00:22:40,570 --> 00:22:42,110
I hunted him down twice

158
00:22:43,180 --> 00:22:44,780
before I finally killed him.

159
00:22:47,310 --> 00:22:48,510
Tell me more details.

160
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:50,840
The first time was

161
00:22:52,110 --> 00:22:54,240
when we killed Zhang Ruipu.

162
00:22:55,460 --> 00:22:56,830
Back then, you

163
00:22:57,920 --> 00:23:00,310
had a little girl with you, right?

164
00:23:02,830 --> 00:23:05,420
While you were negotiating
with Zhang Ruipu,

165
00:23:06,740 --> 00:23:07,820
my people

166
00:23:08,570 --> 00:23:09,980
swapped her out.

167
00:23:53,940 --> 00:23:55,560
That friend of yours

168
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:57,070
is pretty smart.

169
00:23:57,530 --> 00:23:59,400
I still can't figure out

170
00:24:00,140 --> 00:24:01,610
how he learned

171
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:03,400
that Zhang Ruipu and we were

172
00:24:04,010 --> 00:24:05,770
not on the same side.

173
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:08,850
You have no idea

174
00:24:09,980 --> 00:24:12,750
how much effort I put into the plan

175
00:24:14,250 --> 00:24:16,350
to assassinate Zhang Ruipu...

176
00:24:17,790 --> 00:24:18,740
Yet it was almost

177
00:24:19,660 --> 00:24:21,660
ruined by a cripple.

178
00:24:30,380 --> 00:24:31,780
His name is Zhang Haixia.

179
00:24:32,190 --> 00:24:33,520
Keep that in mind.

180
00:24:35,590 --> 00:24:36,380
Speak!

181
00:24:42,980 --> 00:24:44,440
Fortunately,

182
00:24:45,590 --> 00:24:46,950
Zhang Ruipu

183
00:24:47,420 --> 00:24:49,550
was defeated by his own arrogance.

184
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:52,110
He underestimated his enemy.

185
00:24:52,840 --> 00:24:53,850
Then,

186
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:56,110
I started hunting him down.

187
00:25:01,530 --> 00:25:03,880
I found he boarded the Nan'an.

188
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:09,720
The poison was
taking a heavy toll on him back then.

189
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:12,150
We all thought

190
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:14,480
he was done for.

191
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:15,920
But we never thought

192
00:25:16,770 --> 00:25:19,120
that he injured our men

193
00:25:20,030 --> 00:25:22,160
and escaped to the third-class cabin.

194
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:24,210
Your friend is

195
00:25:24,570 --> 00:25:25,850
really something.

196
00:25:26,770 --> 00:25:28,090
Even with broken legs,

197
00:25:28,880 --> 00:25:30,600
he still cornered me

198
00:25:31,220 --> 00:25:32,960
this far.

199
00:25:34,570 --> 00:25:35,480
His death is

200
00:25:36,570 --> 00:25:37,960
such a pity.

201
00:25:50,220 --> 00:25:52,620
Is the one disguised
as Zhang Haijiao dead?

202
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:55,100
You guys once

203
00:25:56,500 --> 00:25:58,280
met in the third-class cabin.

204
00:25:58,660 --> 00:26:01,720
If you haven't found her corpse,

205
00:26:01,940 --> 00:26:03,140
it proves that

206
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:05,200
she has escaped.

207
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:07,510
Do you remember
that assassin named Bai Zhu?

208
00:26:07,510 --> 00:26:09,050
A musketeer wanted
to torture her to death.

209
00:26:09,050 --> 00:26:10,310
Sir, you're mistaken.

210
00:26:10,330 --> 00:26:12,060
Do you know you're going to die?

211
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:25,020
One last question.

212
00:26:27,750 --> 00:26:29,060
Who sent you?

213
00:26:30,810 --> 00:26:33,340
Why did you kill the people
from the Archives?

214
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:40,000
Was it a warlord?

215
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:42,510
I don't know.

216
00:26:44,070 --> 00:26:45,760
I was ordered

217
00:26:46,160 --> 00:26:48,470
to spread the Twilight Grass,

218
00:26:48,740 --> 00:26:51,400
bring all the people
from the Southern Archives

219
00:26:52,980 --> 00:26:54,890
to the Nan'an,

220
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:58,140
and kill them all.

221
00:26:58,480 --> 00:26:59,480
I really

222
00:27:01,240 --> 00:27:02,850
don't know anything else.

223
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:27,490
[The Nan'an]

224
00:27:39,510 --> 00:27:40,010
You...

225
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:42,380
Where have you been?

226
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:44,130
Why are you in such a mess again?

227
00:27:44,700 --> 00:27:45,510
Are you okay?

228
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,720
Miss Dong repeatedly warned us

229
00:27:51,270 --> 00:27:53,180
not to leave this room.

230
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:17,960
Eat as much as you can.

231
00:28:40,780 --> 00:28:42,380
I've known him my whole life.

232
00:28:46,450 --> 00:28:49,250
He used to complain
that I always acted recklessly

233
00:28:49,430 --> 00:28:51,490
without considering consequences,

234
00:28:51,750 --> 00:28:53,010
saying that I would die

235
00:28:53,900 --> 00:28:54,830
sooner or later.

236
00:29:00,410 --> 00:29:01,540
I never expected him

237
00:29:04,430 --> 00:29:05,490
to die first.

238
00:29:10,450 --> 00:29:11,060
Fine.

239
00:29:34,330 --> 00:29:35,140
Oh, shit!

240
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:37,530
This is not over yet.

241
00:29:37,780 --> 00:29:39,710
Those who excavated the shipwreck

242
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:41,960
to look for the Twilight Grass back then

243
00:29:42,790 --> 00:29:44,190
were the warlord forces.

244
00:29:44,800 --> 00:29:47,010
The Evil God is also
related to the warlords.

245
00:29:47,010 --> 00:29:48,150
The Twilight Grass and the Evil God

246
00:29:48,110 --> 00:29:49,080
[Mysterious Poison Is
Proliferating Rapidly]

247
00:29:48,170 --> 00:29:49,640
are wreaking havoc in Nanyang again now.

248
00:29:49,110 --> 00:29:50,300
[Causing Multiple Deaths in Xucheng]

249
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:52,050
And right here on the Nan'an,

250
00:29:52,110 --> 00:29:54,000
[N P]

251
00:29:52,260 --> 00:29:53,510
someone's been hunting down

252
00:29:53,510 --> 00:29:56,510
the Archives agents
investigating the Twilight Grass.

253
00:29:56,510 --> 00:29:58,500
As for what the warlords
in the Panhua Reef Case

254
00:29:58,500 --> 00:30:00,430
want to do with the Twilight Grass,

255
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:02,090
there is no conclusion yet.

256
00:30:02,230 --> 00:30:03,600
Panhua Reef?

257
00:30:04,680 --> 00:30:06,560
I... I think I've heard of it.

258
00:30:06,660 --> 00:30:08,700
Is it that haunted place?

259
00:30:12,060 --> 00:30:13,050
Eat more.

260
00:30:13,170 --> 00:30:14,770
Here, eat more if you can.

261
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:16,010
Have this, too.

262
00:30:22,380 --> 00:30:23,110
Shrimpie,

263
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:27,620
you wouldn't die for nothing.

264
00:30:29,750 --> 00:30:31,860
I will find out the forces behind this

265
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:34,860
and avenge you.

266
00:30:36,850 --> 00:30:38,240
Attention, please.

267
00:30:38,830 --> 00:30:42,360
This voyage is about to reach
the final destination, Xiacheng.

268
00:30:42,750 --> 00:30:48,630
[The Nan'an]

269
00:30:42,980 --> 00:30:44,380
Attention, please.

270
00:30:44,420 --> 00:30:48,770
This voyage is about to reach
the final destination, Xiacheng.

271
00:30:50,510 --> 00:30:52,290
After over a decade,

272
00:30:52,750 --> 00:30:54,590
Zhang Hailou finally came home.

273
00:30:55,220 --> 00:30:58,410
[Xiacheng]

274
00:30:56,460 --> 00:30:57,310
This is also

275
00:30:58,240 --> 00:30:58,960
where everything

276
00:30:58,410 --> 00:31:00,670
[Xiacheng Pier]

277
00:30:58,960 --> 00:31:00,560
about the Southern Archives

278
00:31:01,660 --> 00:31:03,000
began.

279
00:31:25,850 --> 00:31:27,910
I'll hand this over to the ship police

280
00:31:27,940 --> 00:31:29,470
after getting off the ship.

281
00:31:38,250 --> 00:31:38,880
Plague,

282
00:31:39,680 --> 00:31:40,740
we're in Xiacheng.

283
00:31:40,750 --> 00:31:41,720
Let's get off.

284
00:31:47,860 --> 00:31:48,460
Plague...

285
00:31:51,940 --> 00:31:52,590
Plague?

286
00:31:56,970 --> 00:31:57,690
Plague?

287
00:32:02,240 --> 00:32:03,800
Why are you still here?

288
00:32:03,870 --> 00:32:05,540
It's safe.

289
00:32:05,810 --> 00:32:06,610
Relax.

290
00:32:06,610 --> 00:32:09,410
I hear there are
some beautiful girls in Xiacheng.

291
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:10,460
He doesn't know, huh?

292
00:32:10,460 --> 00:32:11,240
I guess so.

293
00:32:26,040 --> 00:32:27,020
Miss Dong.

294
00:32:28,740 --> 00:32:29,650
The ship is about to dock.

295
00:32:29,650 --> 00:32:31,650
You were unwilling to see me before.

296
00:32:32,810 --> 00:32:34,410
May I ask you a few questions?

297
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:39,840
Miss Dong?

298
00:33:30,190 --> 00:33:30,930
Miss Dong,

299
00:33:31,500 --> 00:33:33,410
the captured robbers have

300
00:33:33,590 --> 00:33:34,720
been attacked.

301
00:33:34,720 --> 00:33:35,420
Should we lock down the ship

302
00:33:35,420 --> 00:33:36,660
and find out who it was?

303
00:33:36,660 --> 00:33:37,350
No.

304
00:33:37,850 --> 00:33:39,750
Stick to the original plan.

305
00:33:41,310 --> 00:33:43,040
Whether alive or dead,

306
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:45,160
hand them over to the ship police.

307
00:33:45,700 --> 00:33:46,400
Got it.

308
00:34:11,239 --> 00:34:12,330
Times are hard.

309
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:13,639
Let's part ways here.

310
00:34:14,050 --> 00:34:15,480
If your obsession persists

311
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:17,080
and you are still perplexed,

312
00:34:17,650 --> 00:34:19,179
you may come here for a chat.

313
00:34:19,590 --> 00:34:20,389
But remember,

314
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:21,870
it's best we don't meet.

315
00:34:22,020 --> 00:34:23,750
There's nothing to say anyway.

316
00:36:12,190 --> 00:36:13,040
We're home,

317
00:36:14,170 --> 00:36:14,960
Haixia.

318
00:37:04,880 --> 00:37:07,830
[Welcome]

319
00:37:25,230 --> 00:37:25,880
Shrimpie,

320
00:37:27,050 --> 00:37:28,380
we are back in Xiacheng.

321
00:37:30,010 --> 00:37:33,220
[Xiacheng Pier]

322
00:37:33,600 --> 00:37:34,930
We've finally arrived.

323
00:37:35,240 --> 00:37:36,670
Yeah, I'm exhausted.
